    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Like Mother&mdash;Like Children</strong>&mdash;The tenderest earthly tie is that between the mother and her child. The child is more readily impressed by the life and example of the mother than by that of the father, for a stronger and more tender bond of union unites them.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"2T 536.1\" data-link=\"120.2308\">Testimonies for the Church 2:536</span>.</span></a></sup>",
