    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The thoughts and feelings of the mother will have a powerful influence upon the legacy she gives her child. If she allows her mind to dwell upon her own feelings, if she indulges in selfishness, if she is peevish and exacting, the disposition of her child will testify to the fact. Thus many have received as a birthright almost unconquerable tendencies to evil. The enemy of souls understands this matter much better than do many parents. He will bring his temptations to bear upon the mother, knowing that if she does not resist him, he can through her affect her child. The mother&apos;s only hope is in God. She may flee to Him for strength and grace; and she will not seek in vain.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">5<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"nol-ink\" title=\"ST 9-13-1910\">The Signs of the Times, September 13, 1910</span> (<span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"ST 9-22-1881\" data-link=\"820.3727\">The Signs of the Times, September 22, 1881</span>).</span></a></sup>",
