    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "A Christian mother will ever be wide awake to discern the dangers that surround her children. She will keep her own soul in a pure, holy atmosphere; she will regulate her temper and principles by the word of God and will faithfully do her duty, living above the petty temptations which will always assail her.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 69, 1896\" data-link=\"14061.5033001\">Letter 69, 1896</span>.</span></a></sup>",
