    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The perception of children is quick, and they discern patient, loving tones from the impatient, passionate command, which dries up the moisture of love and affection in the hearts of children. The true Christian mother will not drive her children from her presence by her fretfulness and lack of sympathizing love.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">7<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"ST 9-13-1877\" data-link=\"820.740\">The Signs of the Times, September 13, 1877</span>.</span></a></sup>",
